title: Dublin Core (dc) Metadata schema used by Dataverse
description: The Dublin Core Metadata Initiative (DCMI) supports shared innovation in metadata design and best practices across a broad range of purposes and business models.

items.help_tip: Enter a name for this item.
items.label: Title

items.help_tip: Enter an author for this item. (Lastname/Firstname)
items.label: Creator (comma separated)

items.help_tip: Enter a contact email address for this item.
items.label: Contributor Email

items.help_tip: Describe the purpose, scope or nature of this item.
items.label: Description

items.help_tip: Enter subject from dropdown.
items.label: Subject

items.help_tip: An unambiguous reference to the resource within a given context.
items.label: Identifier

items.help_tip: Person or agency financially or administratively responsible for the Dataset.
items.label: Producer

items.help_tip: Production date of Dataset.
items.label: Production Date

items.help_tip: Type of data included in the file: survey data, census/enumeration data, aggregate data, clinical.
items.label: Kind of Data

items.help_tip: List of books, articles, data files if any that served as the sources for the Dataset.
items.label: Data Sources (comma separated)

items.help_tip: Any related material (journal article citation is not included here - see: isReferencedBy below).
items.label: Related Material (comma separated)

items.help_tip: Information about rights held in and over the resource.
items.label: rights

items.help_tip: Set the license to CC0 (default in Dataverse for new Datasets), otherwise enter “NONE” and fill in the Terms of Use field.
items.label: License

items.help_tip: If not using CC0, enter any terms of use or restrictions for the Dataset.
items.label: Terms of Use

items.help_tip: The publication (journal article, book, other work) that uses this dataset (include citation, permanent identifier (DOI), and permanent URL).
items.label: Referenced by (comma separated)

items.help_tip: The spatial or temporal topic of the resource, the spatial applicability of the resource, or the jurisdiction under which the resource is relevant.
items.label: Coverage

items.help_tip: The file format, physical medium, or dimensions of the resource.
items.label: Format

items.help_tip: A language of the resource.
items.label: Language

items.help_tip: A resource that acts or has the power to act.
items.label: Agent

items.help_tip: A group of agents.
items.label: Agent Class

items.help_tip: The set of regions in space defined by their geographic coordinates according to the DCMI Box Encoding Scheme.
items.label: Box

items.help_tip: The set of classes specified by the DCMI Type Vocabulary, used to categorize the nature or genre of the resource.
items.label: DCMI Type

items.help_tip: The set of conceptual resources specified by the Dewey Decimal Classification.
items.label: DDC

items.help_tip: A digital resource format.
items.label: File Format

items.help_tip: A rate at which something occurs.
items.label: Frequency

items.help_tip: The set of media types specified by the Internet Assigned Numbers Authority.
items.label: IMT

items.help_tip: The extent or range of judicial, law enforcement, or other authority.
items.label: Jurisdiction

items.help_tip: The set of conceptual resources specified by the Library of Congress Classification.
items.label: LLC

items.help_tip: The set of labeled concepts specified by the Library of Congress Subject Headings.
items.label: LCSH

items.help_tip: A legal document giving official permission to do something with a Resource.
items.label: License Document

items.help_tip: A system of signs, symbols, sounds, gestures, or rules used in communication.
items.label: Linguistic System

items.help_tip: A spatial region or named place.
items.label: Location

items.help_tip: A location, period of time, or jurisdiction.
items.label: Location Period Or Jurisdiction

items.help_tip: The set of labeled concepts specified by the Medical Subject Headings.
items.label: MESH

items.help_tip: A file format or physical medium.
items.label: Media Type

items.help_tip: A file format or physical medium.
items.label: Media Type Or Extent

items.help_tip: A method by which resources are added to a collection.
items.label: Method Of Accrual

items.help_tip: A process that is used to engender knowledge, attitudes, and skills.
items.label: Method Of Instruction

items.help_tip: The set of conceptual resources specified by the National Library of Medicine Classification.
items.label: NLM

items.help_tip: The set of time intervals defined by their limits according to the DCMI Period Encoding Scheme.
items.label: Period

items.help_tip: An interval of time that is named or defined by its start and end dates.
items.label: Period Of Time

items.help_tip: A physical material or carrier.
items.label: Physical Medium

items.help_tip: A material thing.
items.label: Physical Resource

items.help_tip: The set of points in space defined by their geographic coordinates according to the DCMI Point Encoding Scheme.
items.label: Point

items.help_tip: A plan or course of action by an authority, intended to influence and determine decisions, actions, and other matters.
items.label: Policy

items.help_tip: A statement of any changes in ownership and custody of a resource since its creation that are significant for its authenticity, integrity, and interpretation.
items.label: Provenance Statement

items.help_tip: A statement about the intellectual property rights (IPR) held in or over a Resource, a legal document giving official permission to do something with a resource, or a statement about access rights.
items.label: Rights Statement

items.help_tip: A dimension or extent, or a time taken to play or execute.
items.label: Size Or Duration

items.help_tip: A basis for comparison; a reference point against which other things can be evaluated.
items.label: Standard

items.help_tip: The set of places specified by the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.
items.label: TGN

items.help_tip: The set of conceptual resources specified by the Universal Decimal Classification.
items.label: UDC

items.help_tip: The set of identifiers constructed according to the generic syntax for Uniform Resource Identifiers as specified by the Internet Engineering Task Force.
items.label: URI

items.help_tip: The set of dates and times constructed according to the W3C Date and Time Formats Specification.
items.label: W3CDTF

items.help_tip: The method by which items are added to a collection.
items.label: Accrual Method

items.help_tip: The frequency with which items are added to a collection.
items.label: Accrual Periodicity

items.help_tip: The policy governing the addition of items to a collection.
items.label: Accrual Policy

items.help_tip: An alternative name for the resource.
items.label: Alternative

items.help_tip: A class or entity for whom the resource is intended or useful.
items.label: Audience

items.help_tip: Date that the resource became or will become available.
items.label: Available

items.help_tip: A bibliographic reference for the resource
items.label: Bibliographic Citation

items.help_tip: An established standard to which the described resource conforms.
items.label: Conforms To

items.help_tip: Date of acceptance of the resource.
items.label: Date Accepted

items.help_tip: Date of copyright.
items.label: Date Copyrighted

items.help_tip: Date Submitted
items.label: Date Submitted

items.help_tip: A class of entity, defined in terms of progression through an educational or training context, for which the described resource is intended.
items.label: Education Level

items.help_tip: The size or duration of the resource.
items.label: Extent

items.help_tip: A related resource that is substantially the same as the pre-existing described resource, but in another format.
items.label: Has Format

items.help_tip: A related resource that is included either physically or logically in the described resource.
items.label: Has Part

items.help_tip: A related resource that is a version, edition, or adaptation of the described resource.
items.label: Has Version

items.help_tip: A process, used to engender knowledge, attitudes and skills, that the described resource is designed to support.
items.label: Instructional Method

items.help_tip: A related resource that is substantially the same as the described resource, but in another format.
items.label: Is Format Of

items.help_tip: A related resource in which the described resource is physically or logically included.
items.label: Is Part Of

items.help_tip: A related resource that references, cites, or otherwise points to the described resource.
items.label: Is Referenced By

items.help_tip: A related resource that supplants, displaces, or supersedes the described resource.
items.label: Is Replaced By

items.help_tip: A related resource that requires the described resource to support its function, delivery, or coherence.
items.label: Is Required By

items.help_tip: A related resource of which the described resource is a version, edition, or adaptation.
items.label: Is Version Of

items.help_tip: Date of formal issuance (e.g., publication) of the resource.
items.label: Date Issued

items.help_tip: The material or physical carrier of the resource.
items.label: Medium

items.help_tip: Date on which the resource was changed.
items.label: Modified

items.help_tip: A statement of any changes in ownership and custody of the resource since its creation that are significant for its authenticity, integrity, and interpretation.
items.label: Provenance

items.help_tip: A related resource that is supplanted, displaced, or superseded by the described resource.
items.label: Replaces

items.help_tip: A related resource that is required by the described resource to support its function, delivery, or coherence.
items.label: Requires

items.help_tip: A person or organization owning or managing rights over the resource.
items.label: Rights Holder

items.help_tip: Spatial characteristics of the resource.
items.label: Spatial

items.help_tip: A list of subunits of the resource.
items.label: Table Of Contents

items.help_tip: Temporal characteristics of the resource.
items.label: Temporal

items.help_tip: Date of validity of a resource.
items.label: Valid
